XXVIII. WE believe that one Day in ſeven, ought to be ſolemnly obſerved in Exod. 20.




the Worſhip of God; and that by Moſes's Law the Jews and proſelyted Strangers were to keep the ſeventh Day: but from the Reſurrection of Chriſt the firſt Day of the Week ought by all Chriſtians to be obſerved Holy to the Lord, that being called the Lord's Day; 
                  Rev. 1. 10. and the firſt time the Church met together after Chriſt's Aſcenſion Act. 2. 1, 2. Acts 20. 7. was on the Day of Pentecoſt, which was the firſt Day of the Week, as Tradition hath handed it down: and on that Day the Church alſo met together to break Bread, and 1 Cor. 16. 2 make Collections for the poor Saints: and no mention is made that any one Goſpel-Church kept the Jewiſh Sabbath in all the New Teſtament. And we believe that an Apoſtolical Precedent is equivalent to an Apoſtolical Precept in this caſe.
